Here the added elements are:

- 3 Firewalls for to anticipate a computer threat.

- 1 SSL (Secure Sockets Layer) for to guarantee confidentiality so that the data is indecipherable for anyone who tries to use it for malicious purposes.
Authentication to verify that it is not a spoofer and
integrity to ensure the integrity of the data, verifying that the data is not tampered with before reaching its intended recipient.

- 3 Monitoring clients, they are there to monitor server status like CPU, memory and disk. Performance of Queries Per Second (QPS).
Alerts for issues like high CPU usage or low disk availability.
And generates periodic reports on server status and performance, to optimize performance.
